pet.name: Tigger
pet.description:
Tigger came to KARE on June 19th, 2014 along with 1 brother and 2 sisters. They were found in an Orlando warehouse under a pallet and no mommy was found. They were about 4 days old. Their estimate birthday is June 16th, 2014. Bree became their surrogate mom.
Tigger is about 1 year and 6 months old. He loves attention. He is friendly, playful and cuddly. He is great with cats, dogs, kids, rabbits, and ferrets.
Tigger is: -Neuter -Tested for Feline Immunodeficiency virus and Feline Leukemia Virus (FIV/FeLV) -Feline Leukemia vaccine with boosters -Feline Viral Calici Rhinotracheitis Panleukopenia (FVCRP) vaccine with boosters -Rabies vaccine -Fecal tests -Deworming -Microchipped -On monthly flea prevention -Fed high quality grain free food -Cared for in a foster home
More photos can be viewed on our facebook page: www.facebook.com/kareofoviedo
Adoption applications are available on our website www.kareoviedo.com
If you want to set up a meet and greet or have any questions please email kareoviedo@gmail.com

pet.name: Panther *COURTESY POST*
pet.description:
I'm a one year old cuddle bug who was abandoned with my pregnant sister. Iâ€™m so thankful for my foster mommy who took us in and already found my sister and her kittens a home. She has taken really good care of me too, but I am not too fond of her 12-year old shih tzu, and her allergies can't handle all the love I have to give. She even got me neutered, vaccinated, and on a flea treatment for my new pet parent(s). My foster mom will also include my litter box and feeding bowls so all you have to do is love me.
I love to nuzzle up close under your chin and I give great paw massages. When I have had a really rough day lounging around, playing with my toys or watching for lizards, I like to lay my head on your chest or just sit on your lap while you read a book or watch television. I am a gentle black cat who just wants to be loved forever.
All I need is a loving forever home, so please contact my foster mommy, Shannon, at 321-287-4235. Vet reference and $30 donation for KARE Oviedo rescue, please.

pet.name: Penny Lane (SD)
pet.description: Penny Lane is friendly and outgoing...a real SWEETHEART! Contact her foster mom directly saradixon@gmail.com for more information. Penny's adoption fee is $50. (Please do not contact the rescue.)

pet.name: Butternut
pet.description:
You can fill out an adoption application online on our official website.
CONTACT HOLLY at hollyluisi@gmail.com This is a courtesy post. Please do not contact the rescue directly. Thanks!
Butternut is an amazingly sweet boy! He was found outdoors but had been owned as he was already neutered. However - and don't let this alarm you -- he is FIV positive. Cats with FIV can live LONG HEALTHY LIVES - if kept INDOORS! (I personally have an FIV cat that is about 12 yrs old!). He did get along with another cat that was found outdoors - but from here on out should only be with other FIV+ cats. Not sure if he gets along with dogs - but he very well might! And FIV can NOT be passed on to dogs. He LOVES his toys, catnip and a lap to sit on. Please email us if you are interested in meeting this wonderful guy! Thanks!
CONTACT HOLLY at hollyluisi@gmail.com This is a courtesy post. Please do not contact the rescue directly. Thanks!

pet.name: KitKat
pet.description:
KitKat is a totally awesome cat. He is currently earning his keep by being a blood donor at a vet hospital. He is so easy-going that anything is fine with him. He loves everyone and any kind of petting and attention. He is such a cool cat that he deserves to retire and have his own cushy home and loving person.
If you think that you might be that person, please contact Murphy Vet Clinic at (407)323-4707 and tell them you're interested in adopting KitKat.

pet.name: Lucy (SD)
pet.description: Lucy is a true LOVE BUG! If you want a lap cat then this sweet girl is the one for you. Contact her foster mom directly saradixon@gmail.com for more information. (Please do not contact the rescue. Thanks!) Lucy's adoption fee is $50.

pet.name: Frito (WG)
pet.description:
CONTACT: wendygeller@earthlink.net Do NOT email the rescue.
This is a courtesy post - Frito and his BFF - who happens to be his sister Skittles- are looking for a home. They are both FIV+ but we are hoping they will shed the virus and be negative in a few month's time like their other siblings. They are friendly and VERY affectionate, get along with other cats and dogs as well! Please email wendygeller@earthlink.net if you feel you can provide a loving home for Skittles and/or Frito! Adoption fee is $50
(The poster personally has an FIV cat that is going on 15yr old - FIV cats can live a very long and healthy life if kept indoors, fed good food and cared for!)

pet.name: Autumn (SD)
pet.description: Autumn is practically perfect in every way! She gets along great with other cats, dogs and kids. She has a mellow personality and loves laying on your lap. Please contact her foster mom directly sara@flyelite.com if you would like to meet this very sweet girl. (Please do not contact the rescue. Thanks!) Autumn's adoption fee is $50.

pet.name: Rudy (wg)
pet.description:
For information or an application please email the foster home directly: wendygeller@earthlink.net
We do not ship out of state. Please note he cannot go to a home with children! Rudy is a very sweet and friendly loving boy who came from the local animal control facility due to biting his owner. He is not too keen on grooming and it is needed at times. He is a beautiful Maine Coon mix! 2.5 yr old. Gets along with other cats and ignores the dogs although at times he will go after one of the more mellow female cats in the foster home. He attaches himself to one person, will sit in a lap any chance he can get and follow that person around! He's the type of cat that will usually give you a warning sign when he's had too much petting / stimulation. At that point, you need to just leave him be. He's been in the foster home several months now without issue. Rudy is neutered, up to date on all shots and his microchipped. His adoption fee is $125.

pet.name: Selena - wg
pet.description:
THIS IS A COURTESY POST - PLEASE EMAIL barbaram@carefelinetnr.org DIRECTLY. Thanks !!
Selena needs a place to call her own! She is a wonderful lap cat and is healthy as can be. Her foster has gotten her to put on some weight and she is a beauty. Selena is 2 years old, already spayed and has been tested for FIV and FeLV and both are negative.
This loving kitty would be a great companion cat for an older person who doesn't want a frisky kitten and prefers a more mellow kitty to hang out with!
Please let me know when you want her to join your family!! barbaram@carefelinetnr.org

pet.name: Laney
pet.description:
Lainey is a sweet adult female who came to the shelter as a stray. She was pregnant at the time, and has since shown an amazingly caring maternal side of herself as she has raised her four kitties. Lainey is an affectionate cat who loves to be scratched under the chin, and purrs loudly to show her appreciation. She is litter box trained and a very clean cat. If you are looking for a sweet companion, Lainey is definitely worth meeting!
Lainey is ready for a home of her own! She is currently in a loving foster home and will be spayed before going to her forever home. If you are interested in meeting Lainey, please reference Laney's ID number A301018 and contact Diane Gagliano at 407-665-5208 or DGagliano@seminolecountyfl.gov
